item.description:
TIL about the FromStr trait in Rust that is implicitly used through str&rsquo;s parse method.
We could have a struct called Period that parses a string like: &ldquo;10 days&rdquo; into Period { value: 10, timeframe: &quot;days&quot; }. The way to use it would be:
let period = &#34;10 days&#34;.parse::&lt;Period&gt;();
